# Newsletter provider configuration for /api/subscribe
# Pick ONE provider by setting NEWSLETTER_PROVIDER, then fill in the matching credentials.
# If NEWSLETTER_PROVIDER is unset or "log", submissions are logged to the server console only.

# Options: log | formspree | resend | mailchimp | buttondown | convertkit
NEWSLETTER_PROVIDER=log

# --- Cloudflare Turnstile (optional) ---
# If both are set, the newsletter form will render a Turnstile widget and the API
# route will verify tokens server-side. Leave unset to skip Turnstile entirely
# (the honeypot + time-trap still apply).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=0x4AAAAAAA_your_site_key
# TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=0x4AAAAAAA_your_secret_key

# --- Formspree ---
# Get a form ID at https://formspree.io (Project -> form endpoint, the part after /f/)
# FORMSPREE_FORM_ID=xxxxxxxx

# --- Resend (audiences) ---
# https://resend.com/audiences
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxx
# RESEND_AUDIENCE_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx

# --- Mailchimp ---
# API key from Account -> Extras -> API keys. Audience ID is the List ID in Audience settings.
# MAILCHIMP_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx-us21
# MAILCHIMP_AUDIENCE_ID=xxxxxxxxxx

# --- Buttondown ---
# https://buttondown.email
# BUTTONDOWN_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# --- ConvertKit ---
# https://app.convertkit.com/account_settings/advanced_settings
# CONVERTKIT_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# CONVERTKIT_FORM_ID=1234567

# Contact form configuration for /api/contact
# Options: log | formspree | resend
CONTACT_PROVIDER=log

# --- Formspree (contact) ---
# Separate form for contact submissions (so you can route them differently).
# CONTACT_FORMSPREE_FORM_ID=xxxxxxxx

# --- Resend (contact) ---
# Uses RESEND_API_KEY (defined above for newsletter) and sends an email.
# CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL=hello@pause-health.ai
# CONTACT_TO_EMAIL=hello@pause-health.ai

# --- Salesforce Agentforce / Embedded Messaging for Web ---
# All four values are surfaced in the Salesforce Setup screen under:
#   Setup -> Embedded Service Deployments -> <your deployment> -> Code Snippet
# They are public deployment metadata (designed to ship in client JS) so it is
# safe to expose them as NEXT_PUBLIC_ vars. Set all four to enable the live
# Agentforce Service Agent on /demo/intake; leave any unset to fall back to the
# Pause-branded scripted intake prototype.
#
# The Pause-Health production deployment was shipped on 2026-06-02 and
# its values are live in the project's Vercel env. To stand up a fresh
# deployment from scratch (for another org, sandbox, etc.) follow
# docs/PHASE_3_RUNBOOK.md, which documents both the wiring steps and the
# two surprises we hit (clientVersion=WebV1 default needing a Tooling API
# v65 PATCH; legacy "HLS - Route to Bot" Omni-Flow on the Messaging
# Channel needing to be swapped for Routing Type = "Agentforce Service
# Agent" -> your agent).
#
# Five non-negotiable prereqs for any deployment:
#   1. Org CORS allowlist (Setup -> CORS) has your origin (https://...).
#   2. Trusted URLs (Setup -> Security -> Trusted URLs) has your origin
#      with CSP Context=All and all CSP directives ticked.
#   3. EmbeddedServiceConfig has AreGuestUsersAllowed=true AND
#      Metadata.clientVersion="WebV2" (PATCH via Tooling API v65+).
#   4. MessagingChannel Session Handler Type = "Flow" pointing at the
#      Pause_Intake_Prechat_Router routing Flow (Phase 18b architecture:
#      the Flow is what writes the hidden prechat dossier onto
#      MessagingSession before handing off to the agent). Direct
#      routing to an Agentforce Service Agent bypasses the Flow and
#      silently drops custom Parameter Mappings -- don't do that.
#   5. Embedded Service Deployment is published (Metadata API deploys
#      of the channel auto-invalidate SCRT2 cache; a manual UI
#      republish is only needed for Setup-UI-driven changes).
#
# Phase 18a + 18b (pre-fill the chat with patient context, and have
# the agent actually use it): the /demo/intake picker calls
# GET /api/intake/prechat-context?personaId=<id>, which resolves the
# patient via the existing Data 360 + Health Cloud grounding pipeline
# and hands ~20 hidden-prechat fields (each clamped to 255 chars per
# Salesforce's channel hard cap) to the Salesforce SDK before the
# conversation begins. Salesforce delivers them to a routing Flow
# (Pause_Intake_Prechat_Router) which writes each to a Pause_<Name>__c
# custom field on the MessagingSession record before transferring to
# the Pause_Health_Intake_Agent. The agent's contextVariables expose
# the fields as $Context.Pause_<Name>, and the agent's topic
# instructions reference them by name to personalize without re-asking.
# Standard fields (_firstName, _lastName) skip the Flow path -- they
# travel through Salesforce's built-in standardParameters mechanism.
# See docs/PHASE_3_RUNBOOK.md section "Phase 18a follow-up" for the
# full architecture diagram, field schema, and 5 architectural
# constraints we hit.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AGENTFORCE_ORG_ID=00Dxx0000000000AAA
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AGENTFORCE_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=Pause_Health_Intake
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AGENTFORCE_SITE_URL=https://your-domain.my.site.com/ESWYourDeploymentName1700000000000
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AGENTFORCE_SCRT2_URL=https://your-domain.my.salesforce-scrt.com

# --- Pause Care Router (Anthropic) ---
# Optional. When ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is set, the Care Router agent at
#   POST /api/agents/care-router/tasks
# calls Anthropic Claude via the @anthropic-ai/sdk. When unset, the
# Care Router falls back to a deterministic Pause policy engine that
# implements the same clinical pathway rubric. Either way the agent
# emits A2A-conformant responses and Agent Fabric trace spans.
#
# PAUSE_CARE_ROUTER_MODEL defaults to claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929 and
# must remain on the model allow-list enforced by the Pause Agent
# Fabric (claude-sonnet-* or claude-opus-* prefixes).
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# PAUSE_CARE_ROUTER_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929

# --- Salesforce Org (real Data 360 grounding for the Care Router) ---
# All three must be set together for the real-org grounding path to activate.
# If any is missing, the Care Router falls back to the deterministic mocked
# grounding in lib/data-360.ts (zero-credential default works locally and in
# every Vercel preview).
#
# Source: Salesforce Setup -> External Client App Manager -> <your app> ->
#         Settings -> OAuth Settings -> Consumer Key and Secret.
# Auth flow: OAuth 2.0 Client Credentials Flow (server-to-server, no user
# redirect). Configured per the policy in Setup -> External Client Apps ->
# Policies (Run-As user must be set and pre-authorized via permission set).
#
# SF_INSTANCE_URL must NOT have a trailing slash. Use the org's My Domain
# URL (e.g. https://yourorg.my.salesforce.com), not login.salesforce.com.
#
# SF_INSTANCE_URL=https://trailsignup-c2d761a3b89bf2.my.salesforce.com
# SF_CLIENT_ID=3MVG9...
# SF_CLIENT_SECRET=ABCDEF...
#
# Optional override; defaults to v60.0 if unset. Bumping this is safe as
# long as the SOQL in lib/salesforce/grounding.ts stays version-compatible.
# SF_API_VERSION=60.0

# --- Salesforce Data Cloud (Phase 2: wearable/EHR Calculated Insights) ---
#
# When SF_DC_TENANT_URL is set, /api/data-360/.../grounding will layer
# three real Data Cloud Calculated Insights on top of the Phase 1 SOQL
# results: HRV RMSSD z-score, vasomotor burden composite, sleep disruption
# index. Without it, those three insights fall back to intake-only baselines.
#
# SF_DC_TENANT_URL is the base URL of your Data Cloud tenant. Pattern:
#   https://<15-char-orgId>.c360a.salesforce.com
# Find it in Setup → Data Cloud → Settings → API Tenant URL, or run:
#   sf data query --query "SELECT Id FROM Organization LIMIT 1" and
#   use the 15-char prefix.
# The same SF_CLIENT_ID / SF_CLIENT_SECRET Connected App is reused —
# no separate credential is required.
#
# SF_DC_TENANT_URL=https://00DHp00000L08KK.c360a.salesforce.com
#
# Optional; defaults to "v1".
# SF_DC_API_VERSION=v1

# --- MuleSoft Anypoint (live Experience-API path for /api/mulesoft/health) ---
# When MULESOFT_HEALTH_BASE_URL is set, /api/mulesoft/health proxies to the
# customer's MuleSoft Experience API deployed on Anypoint Runtime Fabric /
# CloudHub 2.0. When unset, the route serves the deterministic mock in
# frontend/lib/mulesoft-mocks.ts -- this is the documented Phase 0 / public
# prototype default.
#
# The proxy degrades gracefully: any non-2xx, network error, timeout, or
# bad-shape response falls back to the mock automatically and the response
# meta._source flips from "live-mulesoft" to "mock-fallback". See
# frontend/lib/mulesoft/health.ts for the live/mock branching logic and
# frontend/lib/mulesoft/health.test.ts + the route test for the full matrix.
#
# Deploy-side: see docs/MULESOFT_PHASE_1_HANDOFF.md for the Anypoint Code
# Builder walkthrough; the deployable Mule app lives in
# mulesoft/pause-mulesoft-health-v1/.
#
# MULESOFT_HEALTH_BASE_URL=https://pause-mulesoft-health-v1.us-e2.cloudhub.io
#
# Anypoint Platform Connected App (server-to-server OAuth, client credentials).
# Not consumed by the prototype today -- reserved for iteration 2 (API Manager
# policy enforcement, programmatic CloudHub 2.0 deploys from CI). Listed here
# so the env shape is documented for the user's Anypoint org.
#
# Source: Anypoint Platform -> Access Management -> Connected Apps -> New
# Required scopes: View Organization, Read Servers, Manage Applications (CH2)
#
# ANYPOINT_CLIENT_ID=...
# ANYPOINT_CLIENT_SECRET=...
# ANYPOINT_ORG_ID=...
# ANYPOINT_ENV_ID=...
# ANYPOINT_CONTROL_PLANE=https://anypoint.mulesoft.com
# (Use https://eu1.anypoint.mulesoft.com for EU, https://gov.anypoint.mulesoft.com for Gov)
